elevator - Variable in class cw3.Building
The building's elevator
Elevator - Class in cw3
This class denotes an American-style elevator (no 13th floor) with two strategies: Default strategy: Start at the bottom, go to the top and then back to the bottom. Improved strategy: Start from current position and direction; change direction when finished serving customers in that direction; and only go as far as necessary. These two methods (the strategies) return the number of moves it took them to serve all customers.
Elevator(int, int, ArrayList<Customer>) - Constructor for class cw3.Elevator
Takes as arguments: number of floors, bottom floor and a Customer list. Sets the Elevator.bottomFloor, Elevator.numFloors, Elevator.currentFloor and Elevator.customerList. Infers and sets the Elevator.topFloor.
